I've been wrangling with this for quite a while, landed on this today. Drop in for 11ty config.

```
export default async function (eleventyConfig) {
  let internalConfig;
  eleventyConfig.on('eleventy.config', (config) => {
    internalConfig = config;
  });
  eleventyConfig.on('eleventy.beforeWatch', (changedFiles) => {
    if (changedFiles.some((f) => f.endsWith('.webc'))) {
      internalConfig.config.useTemplateCache = false;
    }
  });
}
```

Whatever performance gain I was getting from the template cache was well and truly negated by needing to kill/start the server after each change to a WebC component :)

My local env is a relatively small build, so your mileage may vary.

