content.text:
OK, sorry — I got confused. Looking at the grid system: at 1040px `.g-main` has `--num-cols: 5`, which means 5 columns and 4 gutters. In the formula:

- `4` = number of gutters = `num_cols - 1`
- `5` = number of columns = `num_cols`

So `--target-cols: 4` doesn't map cleanly to either number. I think you'd want `--num-cols: 5` (matching the grid) and derive both from it:

```css
--num-cols: 5;
--p-start: calc(
  var(--g-padding-h) +
    (100vw - 2 * var(--g-padding-h) - (var(--num-cols) - 1) * var(--g-gutter)) / var(--num-cols) +
    var(--g-gutter)
);
```

Then at wider breakpoints you just change `--num-cols` to match (6, 10, 11, etc.).

