content.text:
At 2200px you need to skip 2 columns instead of 1. Your current formula skips 1 column. You'd need a `--skip-cols` variable too. The general formula is:

```css
--p-start: calc(
  var(--g-padding-h) +
    var(--skip-cols) *
    (
      (100vw - 2 * var(--g-padding-h) - (var(--num-cols) - 1) * var(--g-gutter)) /
      var(--num-cols) + var(--g-gutter)
    )
);
```

So at the 2200px breakpoint:

```css
@media (min-width: 2200px) {
  ol {
    --num-cols: 11;
    --skip-cols: 2;
  }
}
```

And update the 1040px definition to set `--skip-cols: 1`, then fold it into the formula. Want me to make the edit?

